1
00:00:00,190 --> 00:00:01,960
I'm afraid my dad might not be okay with it.

2
00:00:02,370 --> 00:00:06,280
You know how fearsome and strict he is.

3
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:07,320
Men being together?

4
00:00:07,370 --> 00:00:08,320
Are you crazy?

5
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:09,160
Believe me!

6
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:11,000
- Break up with him!
- Do I have to?

7
00:00:11,019 --> 00:00:12,339
I don't want to break up with you.

8
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:14,240
I'll hold your hands
and go through this with you.

9
00:00:14,259 --> 00:00:15,900
I know you're disappointed.

10
00:00:15,949 --> 00:00:18,100
So am I.

11
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:21,339
But he's not wrong
for making his own choices, either.

12
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:24,260
Let him make his own decisions, alright?

13
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,609
I'm sorry, honey.

14
00:00:27,219 --> 00:00:29,660
for not listening to you.

15
00:00:31,289 --> 00:00:33,479
- I'm so happy.
- Thank you for understanding me.

16
00:00:35,899 --> 00:00:37,140
You're my son;

17
00:00:37,479 --> 00:00:39,240
of course, I understand you.

18
00:00:39,759 --> 00:00:40,710
Grandpa!

19
00:00:41,030 --> 00:00:41,880
Grandpa!

20
00:01:07,359 --> 00:01:08,359
Grandpa!

21
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,560
Grandpa!

22
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:10,760
Grandpa.

23
00:01:16,079 --> 00:01:16,920
Hello.

24
00:01:16,959 --> 00:01:18,200
Someone is unconscious.

25
00:01:18,239 --> 00:01:19,280
Yes, the address is 11/11.

26
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,200
Please hurry up.

27
00:01:20,239 --> 00:01:20,799
- Grandpa!
- Yes.

28
00:01:22,319 --> 00:01:23,200
- Grandpa.
- Grandpa!

29
00:01:23,359 --> 00:01:24,519
- Please hurry up.
- What happened?

30
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,870
Grandpa.

31
00:01:25,909 --> 00:01:27,180
I just called an ambulance.

32
00:01:27,959 --> 00:01:29,760
[Disclaimer: All depicted events are fictional
and for entertainment purposes only

33
00:01:29,799 --> 00:01:30,680
Viewer discretion is advised]

34
00:03:09,599 --> 00:03:11,319
Mom, how's Grandpa?

35
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,759
He's still in there.

36
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:22,079
I'm sure he will be okay.

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,020
How's Dad?

38
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,240
We're still waiting. He's in there.

39
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,120
- And...
- Here she is.

40
00:03:48,199 --> 00:03:50,479
- Is there a family member of Mr. Kan Nirun here?
- Yes, that's me.

41
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,719
I'm his son.

42
00:03:51,759 --> 00:03:53,159
How is he?

43
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,960
The patient's safe and stable,

44
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:58,199
but the doctor has decided
to admit him for monitoring.

45
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,710
- Okay.
- Anyway, please come this way.

46
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:00,629
Yes, okay.

47
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,000
Just a few more days,

48
00:04:11,039 --> 00:04:13,240
and if everything's alright,
he can go home.

49
00:04:13,479 --> 00:04:17,079
Please avoid letting him stay in the sun
for too long.

50
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,170
Thank you so much, doctor.

51
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,720
Thank you.

52
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:21,600
Goodbye.

53
00:04:25,459 --> 00:04:27,459
I'll go get some food.

54
00:04:27,879 --> 00:04:29,279
Do you have anything in mind?

55
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,189
We're getting some food.

56
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:57,230
Wanna come with us?

57
00:05:02,959 --> 00:05:04,519
We'll catch up with you later.

58
00:05:27,519 --> 00:05:29,199
Are you still in shock?

59
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,839
It's okay.

60
00:06:15,399 --> 00:06:16,779
Muenfah,

61
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,600
thanks a lot for today.

62
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:23,879
Without him, I have no idea
what would've happened to Grandpa.

63
00:06:25,519 --> 00:06:29,079
Actually, your son takes after you in this way,

64
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,800
never showing weakness to anyone

65
00:06:34,158 --> 00:06:35,560
except the one he loves,

66
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,800
and showing strength to the world

67
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,069
not to worry anyone.

68
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:03,160
Why...

69
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,959
don't you take him to Grandpa?

70
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,310
Can I?

71
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,000
You're more than welcome to.

72
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,670
Thank you.

73
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,920
There's no need to stay at the hospital.

74
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,560
It's normal for someone this old to fall.

75
00:07:43,879 --> 00:07:46,279
You need to stay here for now,

76
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:49,120
and when you're back,
I won't let you water the plants anymore.

77
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,560
That'll leave me with nothing to do,
feeling awfully lonely.

78
00:07:54,519 --> 00:07:56,680
I'll stay with you tonight.

79
00:07:56,839 --> 00:07:58,639
You should be with your mom.

80
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,480
What about Mookrob?

81
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:02,759
I bet our house is a mess now,

82
00:08:03,759 --> 00:08:05,759
I'll stay with you, then.

83
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,360
Right, that's great.

84
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:08,629
I'll be with you, too.

85
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,680
You've got work to do.

86
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,920
- What?
- Go finish it.

87
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:12,959
You can come by tomorrow.

88
00:08:16,519 --> 00:08:17,660
Then...

89
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:21,000
can I stay with you and Teerak?

90
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,519
Right, that's nice.

91
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:27,160
So there's someone with Rak here.

92
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:28,959
Hold on, how can he stay?

93
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,069
He didn't bring any clothes for tonight.

94
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,918
For Teerak's clothes and stuff,

95
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,960
I can ask Dom to go get them.

96
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,389
- Right?
- Uh...

97
00:08:36,558 --> 00:08:37,519
Yes.

98
00:08:37,759 --> 00:08:39,279
I'll go get yours, too.

99
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:40,840
Make sure you let your family know.

100
00:08:40,879 --> 00:08:42,399
Okay, thanks.

101
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:44,639
That's settled, then.

102
00:08:44,679 --> 00:08:46,440
If I had gone home,

103
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,799
all of this could've been avoided.

104
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:50,799
You should stay here near the doctor.

105
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,480
I'll be with you, too.

106
00:08:53,519 --> 00:08:54,759
No one thinks it's a big deal.

107
00:08:54,799 --> 00:08:56,070
And you won't feel lonely.

108
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,299
Thanks.

109
00:09:14,279 --> 00:09:16,830
I was in shock, so I forgot to tell you this.

110
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,000
Thank you, Fah.

111
00:09:20,919 --> 00:09:22,320
Without you,

112
00:09:22,879 --> 00:09:24,559
I wouldn't be able to get myself together.

113
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,929
He's always been healthy.

114
00:09:32,879 --> 00:09:36,240
Every day, he would be watering the plants,

115
00:09:36,919 --> 00:09:38,919
taking Mookrob for a walk,

116
00:09:39,399 --> 00:09:42,320
or...playing chess all alone in the yard.

117
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,679
However,

118
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:48,080
taking our family for granted is frightening

119
00:09:49,769 --> 00:09:51,169
since we often don't realize...

120
00:09:51,759 --> 00:09:53,960
how much we neglect them.

121
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,480
Watching him live his life alone

122
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:04,879
and hearing him
play with Mookrob every morning became so normal.

123
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,299
But today,

124
00:10:08,559 --> 00:10:10,159
I had no idea.

125
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,799
I didn't hear him.

126
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,720
If you weren't there...

127
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,600
It's not your fault, Teerak.

128
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,139
It's not anyone's fault.

129
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:27,919
I believe...

130
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,039
no one wanted this to happen.

131
00:10:32,679 --> 00:10:33,840
How about this?

132
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,240
If you and your family let me,

133
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:39,039
I'll play chess with Grandpa,

134
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:41,080
so he won't be lonely.

135
00:10:42,519 --> 00:10:44,000
Thank you.

136
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,610
Your family is my family, too.

137
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,039
Come here.

138
00:11:18,559 --> 00:11:20,960
Who's watching who here?

139
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:24,120
Uh...

140
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,240
I think he'll be up soon.

141
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,120
Do you want to eat anything else?

142
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:30,240
I'll go grab some food for Teerak.

143
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,600
He'll be hungry when he wakes up.

144
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,559
Oh, this is enough for me.

145
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,169
Okay.

146
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,240
I'll be right back.

147
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:50,080
Hey, Muenfah?

148
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:51,960
Oh, hello.

149
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,580
Oh...

150
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,519
You bought them, too?

151
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,200
Yes.

152
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,759
I'm afraid Teerak will be hungry when he's up.

153
00:12:04,679 --> 00:12:06,879
These are also for him.

154
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,730
Thanks a lot for taking care of him

155
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,759
and my family.

156
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,799
It's my pleasure.

157
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,679
Fah!

158
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:24,600
Hi, Dad.

159
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,039
- This looks so good.
- How are you doing?

160
00:12:30,279 --> 00:12:32,360
I'm all good. I wanna go home.

161
00:12:32,519 --> 00:12:33,519
You'll get to go soon.

162
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,980
You're healthy and strong.

163
00:12:35,519 --> 00:12:36,519
Hey, Rak.

164
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,200
If he's allowed to go home tomorrow,

165
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,039
Mom'll cook a big meal to celebrate that.

166
00:12:42,559 --> 00:12:43,639
- Really?
- Yes.

167
00:12:43,679 --> 00:12:44,639
That's nice.

168
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,600
Muenfah,

169
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:53,240
if you're free tomorrow, join us.

170
00:12:54,909 --> 00:12:55,720
Okay.

171
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,960
I'm free.

172
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,419
Here. That's good.

173
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:19,039
Eat up, Grandpa, so you'll get stronger.

174
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,639
I've never felt stronger.

175
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,490
And where's Dom?

176
00:13:25,529 --> 00:13:26,639
He's not joining us?

177
00:13:26,679 --> 00:13:28,480
He has to be with his family today,

178
00:13:28,519 --> 00:13:29,840
- so he couldn't come.
- I see.

179
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,870
Muenfah, eat up.

180
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:35,679
I even asked her to do her best.

181
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,539
It's to thank you for saving me.

182
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,120
You're welcome.

183
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,320
Right,

184
00:13:41,639 --> 00:13:42,899
when you have time,

185
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:45,029
help me plant some trees in the yard.

186
00:13:45,919 --> 00:13:47,389
It's my yard.

187
00:13:47,879 --> 00:13:49,360
I don't care if the others won't let you,

188
00:13:49,399 --> 00:13:50,600
but I do.

189
00:13:57,279 --> 00:13:59,019
Have some protein, too.

190
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:01,000
Here.

191
00:14:01,399 --> 00:14:02,879
Give some to Muenfah if that's too much.

192
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,080
Give it to him yourself, then.

193
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,840
You're right.

194
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:20,629
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

195
00:14:24,879 --> 00:14:26,000
Eat up.

196
00:14:26,039 --> 00:14:27,620
Have some more if it's not enough.

197
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,370
Right, Muenfah.

198
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:36,179
After this meal, I want to talk to you.

199
00:14:37,399 --> 00:14:38,399
Okay.

200
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,840
We may not have had...

201
00:14:56,159 --> 00:14:58,360
many conversations before.

202
00:14:59,559 --> 00:15:03,440
First of all, thank you

203
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:05,200
for saving Grandpa.

204
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:06,769
You're welcome.

205
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,639
I'm willing to.

206
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,559
There's one more thing that's...

207
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,289
very important.

208
00:15:19,159 --> 00:15:27,120
I've hurt you with my actions and words,

209
00:15:30,399 --> 00:15:31,580
and I...

210
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:40,120
really hope you'll be able to forgive me.

211
00:15:42,759 --> 00:15:44,399
I can't forgive you

212
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:49,320
since I was never mad at you.

213
00:15:49,879 --> 00:15:53,200
I know you've done all of that

214
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,399
just because you love Teerak.

215
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,789
Thanks a lot.

216
00:16:07,879 --> 00:16:08,720
Well...

217
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:12,519
In the past,

218
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:17,399
the only thing I cared about
was for him to be happy,

219
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:19,279
be in a complete family,

220
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:22,240
and find someone
who can love him as much as I do.

221
00:16:25,639 --> 00:16:27,039
But I was wrong.

222
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,679
I can see it now.

223
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,789
Each person sees love differently.

224
00:16:37,039 --> 00:16:40,039
You can care for Teerak,

225
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,840
and you've become his source of happiness.

226
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,639
Teerak's grandpa once asked me

227
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,200
what I wanted

228
00:16:50,399 --> 00:16:51,789
and what my intention was.

229
00:16:54,879 --> 00:16:56,679
Many answers just kept coming to my mind.

230
00:16:59,679 --> 00:17:02,759
But I've found the right answer today.

231
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:05,200
It's simple, and it's the only one.

232
00:17:11,559 --> 00:17:15,559
I want Teerak to be happy.

233
00:17:16,358 --> 00:17:17,358
That's all.

234
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:23,900
Muenfah,

235
00:17:25,799 --> 00:17:32,380
please make him feel happy.

236
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,160
I promise

237
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:42,920
to make him the happiest person.

238
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,440
Don't you guys worry.

239
00:17:55,759 --> 00:17:58,319
Everything's gonna be okay. Trust me.

240
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:04,400
They're here!

241
00:18:10,759 --> 00:18:11,480
Uh...

242
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,119
What did you guys talk about?

243
00:18:14,279 --> 00:18:15,960
Nothing much.

244
00:18:16,319 --> 00:18:17,869
I just told him

245
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:21,720
he's welcome to come over anytime,
as often as he likes.

246
00:18:24,599 --> 00:18:26,690
So that means...

247
00:18:27,119 --> 00:18:30,480
you're okay if we date?

248
00:18:32,279 --> 00:18:33,240
Yes.

249
00:18:39,109 --> 00:18:39,920
Yay!

250
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,359
- Thanks, Dad.
- Alright.

251
00:18:45,599 --> 00:18:46,990
Care for each other, okay?

252
00:18:58,359 --> 00:18:59,269
Fah,

253
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,720
what did you guys talk about?

254
00:19:01,759 --> 00:19:02,759
I wanna know.

255
00:19:03,599 --> 00:19:05,400
Your dad told me

256
00:19:06,119 --> 00:19:07,710
he wanted nothing from me

257
00:19:08,799 --> 00:19:11,200
but to see you be the happiest person.

258
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,480
I've never questioned

259
00:19:19,119 --> 00:19:20,519
why your name means "the loved one."

260
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:25,599
It's because you're adored
by everyone in your family.

261
00:19:29,759 --> 00:19:32,160
I'm really happy, you know that?

262
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,000
So am I.

263
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,230
I'm thankful

264
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,759
you came into this world for me to love you.

265
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:50,140
Thank you, too,

266
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:52,279
for being with me through all of this.

267
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,880
Fah,

268
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,430
kiss me on the head.

269
00:20:05,119 --> 00:20:06,119
Please.

270
00:20:06,559 --> 00:20:08,319
Kiss me on the head.

271
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,049
Please.

272
00:20:10,089 --> 00:20:12,490
Can you kiss me on the head?

273
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,420
Fah,

274
00:20:16,519 --> 00:20:17,680
come on.

275
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,250
Please.

276
00:20:20,599 --> 00:20:21,400
Okay.

277
00:20:43,039 --> 00:20:44,160
I did.

278
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,160
Yay, you kissed me on the head!

279
00:21:19,359 --> 00:21:20,440
What is it, dear?

280
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:22,599
What do you want, kiddo?

281
00:21:23,119 --> 00:21:26,930
Fah's told me what you said to him.

282
00:21:28,839 --> 00:21:29,720
So?

283
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:33,160
Thank you so much
for caring about my happiness.

284
00:21:33,400 --> 00:21:37,279
Last night, I slept better than I have in a while.

285
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,559
I love you a lot, Dad.

286
00:21:42,519 --> 00:21:43,920
I love you more.

287
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,839
Having a good time, huh?

288
00:21:54,880 --> 00:21:56,029
- Right.
- Let me see.

289
00:21:56,069 --> 00:21:58,450
- He's being clingy.
- I love you, too.

290
00:21:58,490 --> 00:21:59,500
There you go.

291
00:21:59,839 --> 00:22:00,799
What about your sister?

292
00:22:00,839 --> 00:22:02,410
I love you, too.

293
00:22:04,789 --> 00:22:06,029
- Does it smell good?
- How nice.

294
00:22:06,069 --> 00:22:07,470
- That's a lot.
- Guess who I'm giving them to.

295
00:22:07,680 --> 00:22:08,400
These...

296
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,839
You guys were hugging.

297
00:22:09,880 --> 00:22:10,609
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

298
00:22:10,650 --> 00:22:11,650
- Hello.
- Hi.

299
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:15,279
