a free meal or something?

351
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,400
Gosh, I'm just happy for him.

352
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:41,960
We need to celebrate this.

353
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,839
- Right?
- I'm also thinking about a celebration.

354
00:25:44,279 --> 00:25:45,279
See?

355
00:25:45,559 --> 00:25:46,940
What's the occasion?

356
00:25:47,279 --> 00:25:48,920
I can't tell you yet. It's a secret.

357
00:25:49,599 --> 00:25:51,599
- That's nice. Let's...
- No.

358
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:53,680
Let them go by themselves.

359
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,200
They're a couple, but who are you?

360
00:25:56,319 --> 00:25:57,319
Stop it.

361
00:25:57,839 --> 00:25:58,839
Come on, let's go to class.

362
00:25:59,079 --> 00:26:00,279
Fine, see you.

363
00:26:00,319 --> 00:26:02,240
Okay. I'll take Teerak to class first,
and I'll be right there.

364
00:26:02,509 --> 00:26:03,819
Alright, Mr. Madly in Love.

365
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:05,539
Hold on.

366
00:26:06,039 --> 00:26:07,039
What do you want?

367
00:26:07,319 --> 00:26:08,319
Take me with you.

368
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:10,759
Got it.

369
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,119
Come here.

370
00:26:12,849 --> 00:26:14,049
See you.

371
00:26:16,799 --> 00:26:18,599
- Let's go. I'll walk you there.
- Okay.

372
00:26:18,930 --> 00:26:19,730
Let's go.

373
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:24,519
Right,

374
00:26:25,079 --> 00:26:26,160
Fah...

375
00:26:26,759 --> 00:26:29,039
are you really taking me to a celebration?

376
00:26:29,079 --> 00:26:29,960
Yes.

377
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:31,440
Where?

378
00:26:31,559 --> 00:26:33,359
I can't tell you that. It's a secret.

379
00:26:38,359 --> 00:26:39,559
Are you coming or not?

380
00:26:41,119 --> 00:26:42,190
- Yes, right?
- Let's go.

381
00:26:58,799 --> 00:26:59,680
Ghlai.

382
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:02,529
Oh, why are you here?

383
00:27:04,279 --> 00:27:05,660
I'm here to see you.

384
00:27:18,349 --> 00:27:20,200
I was gonna ask

385
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:23,640
if you have any plans for the New Year?

386
00:27:28,519 --> 00:27:29,720
If you don't,

387
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,609
I want you to come with me.

388
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:33,880
Can you?

389
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:38,500
Teerak told you to ask me?

390
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,160
No, he didn't.

391
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,730
It's me

392
00:27:43,920 --> 00:27:44,960
who wanted to ask you that.

393
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:52,569
If it's you, I'm alright.

394
00:27:55,559 --> 00:27:56,559
Is that a yes?

395
00:27:57,200 --> 00:27:58,089
Yes.

396
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,359
Are you going somewhere?

397
00:28:03,920 --> 00:28:04,960
Mm...

398
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:07,230
I think I'm going to a supermarket.

399
00:28:07,799 --> 00:28:08,839
I ran out of shampoo.

400
00:28:09,119 --> 00:28:10,720
I know a good shampoo brand.

401
00:28:12,319 --> 00:28:13,440
- GO HAIR?
- GO HAIR.

402
00:28:16,559 --> 00:28:19,319
Teerak also told you about that?

403
00:28:20,359 --> 00:28:21,369
No.

404
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:23,519
I think we read each other's mind.

405
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,839
Fah, come on.

406
00:29:03,160 --> 00:29:04,980
Is this the secret you talked about?

407
00:29:07,359 --> 00:29:09,400
I knew it since we were in the car.

408
00:29:10,400 --> 00:29:11,390
Do you like it?

409
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,440
I do!

410
00:29:14,599 --> 00:29:15,910
You know what?

411
00:29:16,119 --> 00:29:18,799
I've always loved the view
of the sky meeting the sea,

412
00:29:19,519 --> 00:29:22,440
but now, it means so much more to me.

413
00:29:23,039 --> 00:29:24,079
Why is that?

414
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,210
Because...

415
00:29:26,250 --> 00:29:28,960
it reminds me of your tattoo.

416
00:29:31,319 --> 00:29:34,359
Which one do you like better:
me or my tattoo?

417
00:29:38,799 --> 00:29:40,599
I love you,

418
00:29:42,480 --> 00:29:45,200
so I like your tattoo.

419
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:47,200
But...

420
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,240
I like you better.

421
00:29:55,039 --> 00:29:56,039
Uh...

422
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,920
Wait, Fah!

423
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:02,000
I'll go into the sea.

424
00:30:03,440 --> 00:30:04,559
Hold on.

425
00:30:06,279 --> 00:30:08,079
Aren't you going to change?

426
00:30:09,079 --> 00:30:09,880
Well...

427
00:30:10,359 --> 00:30:11,559
Why do I need to?

428
00:30:12,079 --> 00:30:13,400
It's too sexy. I'm jealous.

429
00:30:14,759 --> 00:30:16,559
Um...how about this?

430
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,519
Hey!

431
00:30:18,559 --> 00:30:21,279
You'll be naked, then.

432
00:30:23,279 --> 00:30:24,279
Isn't that great?

433
00:30:24,599 --> 00:30:26,000
That way, I'll get to show my tattoo, too.

434
00:30:28,359 --> 00:30:29,930
Well...

435
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:33,480
I'd like to be the only one who sees it.

436
00:30:40,319 --> 00:30:41,420
Fah!

437
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,920
Let's get into the sea.

438
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:48,660
Come on.

439
00:31:56,599 --> 00:31:58,059
Anyway,

440
00:31:59,200 --> 00:32:01,000
the New Year is just a week away.

441
00:32:02,279 --> 00:32:03,849
Should we...

442
00:32:05,279 --> 00:32:07,640
get our families together?

443
00:32:09,319 --> 00:32:10,269
Sure.

444
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:16,220
Can I invite my friends, too?

445
00:32:16,259 --> 00:32:17,250
Yes.

446
00:32:17,839 --> 00:32:19,069
How about...

447
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,019
having dinner with our families first

448
00:32:21,059 --> 00:32:22,859
and hanging out with our friends at night?

449
00:32:23,119 --> 00:32:24,329
Does that sound good?

450
00:32:24,839 --> 00:32:27,920
Sure, so we're having dinner
with our families first.

451
00:32:28,039 --> 00:32:28,910
Okay.

452
00:33:06,880 --> 00:33:08,980
Here you go.

453
00:33:20,960 --> 00:33:22,559
You'll get drunk drinking that much alcohol.

454
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:26,190
It's okay. I'm allowed to drink it.

455
00:33:26,720 --> 00:33:29,559
Are you turning red because of this,

456
00:33:30,160 --> 00:33:33,119
or is it because of me?

457
00:33:36,799 --> 00:33:39,130
Your pickup lines are a lot better now.

458
00:33:42,119 --> 00:33:43,920
They're only for you.

459
00:34:05,279 --> 00:34:06,680
What is it?

460
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:24,880
Whoa.

461
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,030
Do you feel dizzy?

462
00:36:00,199 --> 00:36:01,400
It's just that...

463
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:04,400
I can feel the heat in my cheeks.

464
00:36:23,239 --> 00:36:24,960
Can you still feel it?

465
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:30,659
Do you want me to help cool you down?

466
00:36:34,599 --> 00:36:35,800
How?

467
00:36:54,440 --> 00:36:56,420
Will this...

468
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:58,789
cool me down

469
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,420
or heat things up?

470
00:37:28,679 --> 00:37:30,079
Muenfah,

471
00:37:31,239 --> 00:37:33,079
you're so gorgeous.

472
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:36,760
How come you're mine?

473
00:37:41,119 --> 00:37:41,780
You're right.

474
00:37:43,800 --> 00:37:45,389
I'm all yours.

475
00:37:46,039 --> 00:37:47,440
You belong to me.

476
00:37:48,210 --> 00:37:49,409
That means...

477
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,800
I can do whatever I want with you, right?

478
00:39:07,519 --> 00:39:12,239
[Love]

479
00:43:43,119 --> 00:43:44,219
Honey,

480
00:43:44,519 --> 00:43:45,920
is Babe not home yet?

481
00:43:46,239 --> 00:43:47,519
She's on her way.

482
00:43:47,559 --> 00:43:49,960
- Dom's taking her here.
- I see.

483
00:43:50,800 --> 00:43:52,440
Hey,

484
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:54,920
New Year's approaching.

485
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,780
- Mm.
- Where should we hold a party this year?

486
00:43:58,400 --> 00:43:59,440
- Right.
- Right.

487
00:43:59,880 --> 00:44:01,079
Wait, I forgot.

488
00:44:02,119 --> 00:44:03,480
Fah asked me to invite you all.

489
00:44:04,079 --> 00:44:05,269
Invite us to?

490
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:07,920
He wants our families to meet

491
00:44:07,960 --> 00:44:08,960
on New Year's,

492
00:44:09,199 --> 00:44:11,119
so I suggested hosting it at our place.

493
00:44:12,400 --> 00:44:13,849
That sounds good.

494
00:44:13,880 --> 00:44:17,320
Aren't you going to party somewhere else?

495
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:20,349
I want to have dinner with you all first,

496
00:44:20,760 --> 00:44:22,280
and I'll meet up with my friends at night.

497
00:44:23,199 --> 00:44:24,920
What do you guys think?

498
00:44:25,360 --> 00:44:26,389
What do you think?

499
00:44:26,639 --> 00:44:28,039
That's fine by me.

500
00:44:28,639 --> 00:44:29,840
Okay, deal.

501
00:44:30,449 --> 00:44:31,050
OK.

502
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:33,730
That's settled, then.

503
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:34,780
Okay.

504
00:44:39,599 --> 00:44:40,440
[Sunday, December 22, 03:22 P.M.]

505
00:44:44,750 --> 00:44:46,039
- Hey.
- What?

506
00:44:46,079 --> 00:44:47,800
That's a big bite.

507
00:44:47,840 --> 00:44:48,510
Rak!

508
00:44:49,039 --> 00:44:50,300
Where are you going?

509
00:44:52,960 --> 00:44:53,760
Well,

510
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:57,159
Rak's become a homebody recently.

511
00:44:57,199 --> 00:44:57,960
[December]

512
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,650
I think he's working on something, though.

513
00:45:00,690 --> 00:45:01,949
It's suspicious.

514
00:45:26,679 --> 00:45:27,719
What is he doing?

515
00:45:27,760 --> 00:45:29,119
It's been days.

516
00:45:31,559 --> 00:45:32,760
How would I know that?

517
00:45:33,119 --> 00:45:34,119
I'm right here with you.

518
00:45:41,960 --> 00:45:43,250
What are you doing with that phone?

519
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,469
Texting someone?

520
00:45:49,199 --> 00:45:50,679
I'm getting you a concert ticket.

521
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:52,320
You want it, don't you?

522
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:56,559
That's fine, then.

523
00:45:56,920 --> 00:45:58,639
What? You're jealous?

524
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,400
Nope.

525
00:46:05,039 --> 00:46:07,039
Hey, but...

526
00:46:07,320 --> 00:46:09,050
for this concert,

527
00:46:11,880 --> 00:46:14,849
I no longer want to go there with you
as a friend.

528
00:46:18,800 --> 00:46:19,829
And?

529
00:46:20,880 --> 00:46:22,320
You know what I mean.

530
00:46:25,239 --> 00:46:26,239
I'm not listening.

531
00:46:33,039 --> 00:46:34,119
Will you be my boyfriend?

532
00:46:35,280 --> 00:46:36,699
What? I didn't hear you.

533
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:41,519
I said, "Will you be my boyfriend?"

534
00:46:45,559 --> 00:46:47,800
Don't you think you should've asked me nicely?

535
00:46:50,480 --> 00:46:51,679
Hia,

536
00:46:52,519 --> 00:46:53,719
will you be my boyfriend, please?

537
00:47:07,480 --> 00:47:08,440
Yeah.

538
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:16,320
What?

539
00:47:16,960 --> 00:47:17,960
I won't say that twice.

540
00:47:21,400 --> 00:47:22,599
Yeah, I do.

541
00:47:44,440 --> 00:47:45,440
Fah,

542
00:47:47,039 --> 00:47:48,239
I'm taken.

543
00:47:57,199 --> 00:47:59,320
Hey, baby, where are you going?

544
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,199
Hello, Teerak.

545
00:48:11,320 --> 00:48:12,320
What are you doing?

546
00:48:12,440 --> 00:48:15,440
I'm reading about the benefits
of this GO HAIR serum.

547
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:17,039
My mom bought it for me.

548
00:48:17,289 --> 00:48:18,719
This will stop my hair from stinking.

549
00:48:18,880 --> 00:48:20,070
And...

550
00:48:21,039 --> 00:48:23,320
I'm thinking of you.

551
00:48:25,119 --> 00:48:26,599
So am I.

552
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:30,099
Have you brought up the New Year's party
with your parents yet?

553
00:48:30,639 --> 00:48:32,800
I have, and everyone's okay.

554
00:48:32,960 --> 00:48:33,840
You?

555
00:48:33,880 --> 00:48:35,360
My family has agreed as well.

556
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:37,000
That's nice.

557
00:48:37,199 --> 00:48:38,670
I can't wait.

558
00:48:50,639 --> 00:48:51,519
Let's go.

559
00:48:54,519 --> 00:48:56,079
Hi, Dad. Hi, Mom.

560
00:48:56,119 --> 00:48:57,920
- Hi.
- Good evening.

561
00:48:57,960 --> 00:49:01,239
These fruits are for your family.

562
00:49:01,280 --> 00:49:02,480
Thanks, Mom.

563
00:49:02,519 --> 00:49:04,760
I actually asked Lee to join us,

564
00:49:04,800 --> 00:49:06,519
but he has to go with his friend.

565
00:49:06,559 --> 00:49:08,019
That's okay. I get it.

566
00:49:08,400 --> 00:49:10,159
Let's get inside, shall we?

567
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:12,079
Everything's set up in the yard.

568
00:49:13,800 --> 00:49:14,920
We're sorry to bother you.

569
00:49:15,039 --> 00:49:16,039
Please don't be. It's my pleasure.

570
00:49:17,199 --> 00:49:18,340
Please make yourselves at home.

571
00:49:18,380 --> 00:49:20,380
Let me know if you want anything.

572
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:22,869
All the dishes look fantastic.

573
00:49:24,119 --> 00:49:27,000
Fah always says
this family cooks amazing food.

574
00:49:27,039 --> 00:49:29,320
I'll have to ask for your recipe one day.

575
00:49:29,360 --> 00:49:31,400
I'm willing to give it to you.

576
00:49:32,800 --> 00:49:34,440
Seeing the kids happy

577
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:35,920
puts my mind at ease.

578
00:49:35,960 --> 00:49:38,599
That's all we want as a parent.

579
00:49:40,840 --> 00:49:43,559
Muenfah is lucky to have met Teerak.

580
00:49:44,039 --> 00:49:47,119
I was worried
that he wouldn't open up to anyone.

581
00:49:47,440 --> 00:49:48,849
Thought he would end up alone.

582
00:49:48,889 --> 00:49:51,119
Whoa.

583
00:49:51,159 --> 00:49:52,519
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

584
00:49:52,559 --> 00:49:53,519
Let's say...

585
00:49:53,619 --> 00:49:56,909
they're both lucky to have found each other.

586
00:49:59,840 --> 00:50:01,880
Let's dig in, shall we?

587
00:50:01,920 --> 00:50:04,400
The kids will hang out later, too.

588
00:50:04,559 --> 00:50:06,039
- Oh, yeah?
- That's right.

589
00:50:06,239 --> 00:50:09,480
You guys can leave after this meal.

590
00:50:09,519 --> 00:50:11,719
Dad and I will stay here

591
00:50:11,760 --> 00:50:14,360
and talk to Teerak's family.

592
00:50:14,840 --> 00:50:15,719
Please.

593
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:17,139
Sure. Don't worry.

594
00:50:17,179 --> 00:50:17,989
Let's eat.

595
00:50:18,030 --> 00:50:21,719
Alright, let's have our dinner now.

596
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:23,079
- Please enjoy.
- Let's eat.

597
00:50:23,119 --> 00:50:24,480
What should we try first?

598
00:50:24,519 --> 00:50:25,099
This one.

599
00:50:25,139 --> 00:50:25,760
- What is it?
- Satay...

600
00:50:25,800 --> 00:50:26,639
- Here.
- What is it?

601
00:50:26,679 --> 00:50:28,039
- Wow!
- Okay.

602
00:50:28,079 --> 00:50:29,400
Okay, take some.

603
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:30,280
- Should Grandpa take some first?
- Grandpa, grab some.

604
00:50:30,320 --> 00:50:31,079
- Sure.
- Here you go.

605
00:50:31,119 --> 00:50:32,199
Here you are.

606
00:50:32,239 --> 00:50:33,480
- Do you want some sauce, too?
- Thank you.

607
00:50:33,519 --> 00:50:34,309
Have some, Dad.

608
00:50:34,349 --> 00:50:36,289
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

609
00:50:36,329 --> 00:50:38,420
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

610
00:50:39,000 --> 00:50:40,079
Rak, here.

611
00:50:41,440 --> 00:50:42,639
Let's get changed,

612
00:50:42,679 --> 00:50:43,760
or we'll be late.

613
00:50:43,800 --> 00:50:45,840
No one takes longer than you.

614
00:50:45,880 --> 00:50:46,880
Hurry.

615
00:50:48,559 --> 00:50:50,159
Come on, I've already put on my makeup.

616
00:50:50,599 --> 00:50:51,820
- Fah.
- Yes?

617
00:50:52,400 --> 00:50:53,840
I have a surprise for you.

618
00:50:54,159 --> 00:50:55,079
What is it?

619
00:50:56,400 --> 00:50:57,400
Here!

620
00:51:02,000 --> 00:51:03,199
Do you like it?

621
00:51:04,159 --> 00:51:05,349
I love it.

622
00:51:06,000 --> 00:51:06,719
Right,

623
00:51:07,199 --> 00:51:08,679
I also have a surprise for you.

624
00:51:09,039 --> 00:51:10,039
Show me.

625
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:11,280
Not yet.

626
00:51:11,320 --> 00:51:12,119
What?

627
00:51:13,679 --> 00:51:15,119
I'll show you when we're on the cruise.

628
00:51:16,039 --> 00:51:17,260
Okay.

629
00:51:17,300 --> 00:51:18,719
Let's go get changed, shall we?

630
00:51:19,840 --> 00:51:20,789
Let's go.

631
00:51:20,829 --> 00:51:23,030
Where are your clothes?

632
00:51:23,239 --> 00:51:24,239
In the car.

633
00:51:29,000 --> 00:51:31,590
Why is it taking so long? I'm starving.

634
00:51:31,800 --> 00:51:33,989
Jeez, why would you be upset?

635
00:51:34,960 --> 00:51:37,559
I told you to have some food before we came,
but you didn't listen.

636
00:51:39,360 --> 00:51:40,679
Can you stop being so fussy now?

637
00:51:41,119 --> 00:51:42,559
I've never been mean to you,

638
00:51:42,599 --> 00:51:43,800
but you're going too far.

639
00:51:45,079 --> 00:51:46,079
Fine,

640
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:49,960
I'll let you have something tasty tonight.

641
00:51:54,559 --> 00:51:55,960
After the party, though.

642
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,400
Tempting me and running away,

643
00:51:58,440 --> 00:51:59,320
lover boy?

644
00:51:59,760 --> 00:52:02,059
What's wrong with it?
I'm trying to be hard to get.

645
00:52:03,280 --> 00:52:04,440
What's really on your mind?

646
00:52:06,480 --> 00:52:07,760
"Calm down, Hia.

647
00:52:07,880 --> 00:52:09,400
You can't let him get you that easily."

648
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:11,360
Wait, no.

649
00:52:12,119 --> 00:52:13,760
I heard all of that.

650
00:52:15,960 --> 00:52:17,480
It's surprising you're acting this way.

651
00:52:17,679 --> 00:52:18,679
Keep doing it, okay?

652
00:52:19,079 --> 00:52:20,079
It's adorable.

653
00:52:20,519 --> 00:52:21,679
Do you like it?

654
00:52:22,239 --> 00:52:23,639
It makes my heart skip a beat.

655
00:52:24,320 --> 00:52:25,320
What do you think?

656
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:28,880
I'm the best.

657
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:32,500
Give me a reward, big boy.

658
00:52:41,440 --> 00:52:44,039
When it comes to you,
I have no reason to say no.

659
00:52:44,440 --> 00:52:45,440
I'm willing to do anything,

660
00:52:46,199 --> 00:52:47,039
asshole.

661
00:52:48,599 --> 00:52:50,239
So you can speak your mind now?

662
00:52:50,639 --> 00:52:53,829
It should be me saying that to you.

663
00:52:54,480 --> 00:52:56,679
Our communication skills are improving,
and so are our kisses.

664
00:56:49,679 --> 00:56:51,260
When did you set all of this up?

665
00:56:52,320 --> 00:56:53,400
It's a secret.

666
00:56:53,599 --> 00:56:54,599
Do you like it?

667
00:56:58,119 --> 00:56:59,519
It's beautiful.

668
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:03,400
I've got you a gift.

669
00:57:21,559 --> 00:57:24,760
[A gift for "Teerak"]

670
00:57:26,400 --> 00:57:32,000
♫It feels like the same old,
same old, familiar days♫

671
00:57:33,000 --> 00:57:39,320
♫There's something
that makes my heart drift away♫

672
00:57:39,599 --> 00:57:45,000
♫These familiar scenes
never fail to fascinate me, I dare say♫

673
00:57:46,070 --> 00:57:52,070
♫They always make my heart return to the first day♫

674
00:57:52,230 --> 00:57:55,550
♫Every time you smile, it always makes me shy♫

675
00:57:55,590 --> 00:57:58,869
♫Seeking for your sight, my thoughts fly♫

676
00:57:58,909 --> 00:58:02,150
♫I wish to stop the time, never saying goodbye♫

677
00:58:02,190 --> 00:58:04,590
♫Fall and fall in love♫

678
00:58:04,630 --> 00:58:09,829
♫How many more times will I fall for you?♫

679
00:58:09,869 --> 00:58:13,630
♫You always make my heart feel true♫

680
00:58:13,670 --> 00:58:17,679
♫You're the one, my love's always been for you♫

681
00:58:17,719 --> 00:58:23,079
♫For the rest of my life,
I'll spend each day loving you♫

682
00:58:23,119 --> 00:58:27,719
♫No matter how long or what we go through,♫

683
00:58:28,159 --> 00:58:33,559
♫I'll keep falling in love if it's with you♫

684
00:58:36,719 --> 00:58:43,519
♫Fall and fall in love, love, love, love♫

685
00:58:55,199 --> 00:58:57,239
Did you do all the editing?

686
00:58:57,420 --> 00:58:58,630
Yes, I did.

687
00:58:59,440 --> 00:59:01,159
I made this for you.

688
00:59:03,039 --> 00:59:04,039
Thank you so much.

689
00:59:04,960 --> 00:59:06,170
I really like it.

690
00:59:07,119 --> 00:59:08,929
There's one more thing I have for you.

691
00:59:21,199 --> 00:59:22,440
Is this for me?

692
00:59:22,760 --> 00:59:23,760
Yes.

693
00:59:24,360 --> 00:59:25,519
Try it on.

694
00:59:44,280 --> 00:59:45,559
Thank you so much.

695
00:59:46,500 --> 00:59:48,800
Thank you, too, for agreeing to be my boyfriend.

696
00:59:50,519 --> 00:59:51,639
Not just "agreeing."

697
00:59:52,119 --> 00:59:53,320
I love you.

698
00:59:55,000 --> 00:59:55,989
I'm into you.

699
00:59:56,030 --> 00:59:58,230
Whether it's a bright day or a stormy one,

700
00:59:58,719 --> 01:00:00,130
through every high and low,

701
01:00:00,719 --> 01:00:03,519
you'll always be my sky.

702
01:00:06,320 --> 01:00:08,320
From now on,

703
01:00:08,920 --> 01:00:11,320
I'll call you...

704
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:14,000
my "Sky."

705
01:00:15,880 --> 01:00:17,059
So...

706
01:00:18,079 --> 01:00:20,119
I'll call you my "Sea."

707
01:00:38,519 --> 01:00:40,320
I never wished for anything on New Year's,

708
01:00:41,360 --> 01:00:42,860
but this year,

709
01:00:45,039 --> 01:00:48,639
I wish for us to wake up together
every morning,

710
01:00:52,360 --> 01:00:55,360
share smiles every day,

711
01:00:57,719 --> 01:00:59,320
and stay together

712
01:01:00,280 --> 01:01:02,840
through every moment, good or bad.

713
01:01:03,440 --> 01:01:05,440
I love you, my Sea.

714
01:01:06,119 --> 01:01:07,320
I really do.

715
01:01:07,800 --> 01:01:09,960
I love you so much, too, my Sky.

716
01:01:40,710 --> 01:01:42,400
What are you doing?

717
01:01:51,159 --> 01:01:52,760
Look at that, Fah.

718
01:01:54,239 --> 01:01:55,480
They're stunning.
